This directory contains application assets loaded by the WebView.

License classification by file:
  - chess.html: Combined work (AGPL v3 + GPL v3)
      Built from chess.src/ modules by build-chess.py.
      The HTML/CSS template is AGPL v3; the embedded JavaScript modules
      include GPL v3 (DroidFish-derived) and AGPL v3 (original) code.
      See chess.src/README.license for per-module details.
  - stats.html: GPL v3 (PGN parsing derived from DroidFish)
      Fullscreen statistics page (📊统计). Contains time-management analysis,
      clickable variation moves, FEN panel, FEN-embedded PGN support,
      static HTML export dialog with GPL v3 notice. PGN parsing logic
      derived from DroidFish GameTree/PgnToken/PgnScanner (GPL v3).
  - AGPLv3_Logo.svg: FSF official AGPL v3 logo
      Used for license identification on the About page.
      Source: https://www.gnu.org/graphics/agplv3-with-text-162x68.png
  - GPLv3_Logo.svg: FSF official GPL v3 logo
      Used for license identification on the 💾HTML export dialog.
      Source: https://www.gnu.org/graphics/gplv3-127x51.png
  - chess.src/: Source modules (see chess.src/README.license)

v1.0.2 changes reflected in chess.html (rebuilt from chess.src/):
  - ECO opening auto-fill: when a new game starts with a selected ECO
    opening whose `moves` array contains full move data, the moves are
    auto-filled into moveRecords with proper SAN notation — no "..."
    placeholder is needed even when the opening's last move was Black's.
  - Black-to-move opening placeholder: for FEN/setup/PGN imports with
    Black to move (no ECO moves), a null placeholder is prepended to
    moveRecords so Black's first move lands in the Black slot.
  - PGN export evaluation annotations: _buildPGNString() now appends
    `{score eval_word}` after every move with a cached eval, and
    `{SF18 D22 +1.0 8%W/91%D/1%L}` every 5 moves (engine name, depth,
    score, WDL).
  - "Play Again" button now shows ⚔️ prefix (consistent with the
    New Game button).
  - Redo no longer triggers AI (prevents redo-stack corruption).
  - Settings import via file picker no longer shows a duplicate toast
    (the onSettingsImported callback is the single source of truth).

See the root-level LICENSE-AGPL v3, LICENSE-GPL v3, and NOTICE files
for full license texts and attribution details.

v1.0.2 NEW FEATURE additions:
  - stats.html: GPL v3 (PGN parsing derived from DroidFish)
      Fullscreen statistics page opened by the 📊统计 button. Renders the
      current game's PGN with rich formatting (piece symbols, comments,
      variations) and computes statistics (material balance, eval trend,
      move quality classification, accuracy).
      PGN parsing logic (parsePGN function) is derived from DroidFish
      GameTree/PgnToken/PgnScanner (Copyright (C) Peter Österlund, GPL v3).
      Modifications Copyright (C) 2026 Regalia.
      License: GPL v3 (to match the DroidFish-derived PGN parsing code).
      v1.0.2 updates:
        - parsePGN() now prefers _payload.moveRecords (authoritative move
          list from the main app) over re-parsing the PGN string. The
          simplified SAN parser's cascade-failure bug capped total moves
          at ~98; using the authoritative move list fixes this.
        - renderPGNText() piece symbols now use the same color/stroke/glow
          as the main board (wrapped in <span class="piece-white/black">
          with higher CSS specificity than .pgn-display .move).
        - 📂 Select PGN File opens SAF picker directly from StatsActivity
          (no longer bounces through MainActivity).

v1.0.4 EXPANSION (this round) changes (reflected in stats.html and rebuilt chess.html):
  - chess.src/worker-pool.js (NEW FILE): Web Worker pool for PGN parsing,
      statistics computation, and control-map computation. Created via
      Blob URL (compatible with WebView CSP). Inline fallback when Workers
      unavailable. AGPL v3 (original code).
  - chess.src/pgn-standard.js (EXPANDED): added formatEmtTag() for
      [%emt HH:MM:SS]; NAG support (NAG_MAP, nagToSymbol, symbolToNag,
      formatNagToken); visual annotations (formatCslTag, formatCalTag,
      parseCslTag, parseCalTag); TimeControl parsing/formatting
      (parseTimeControl, formatTimeControl) for all 6 spec formats.
  - chess.src/ui.js (EXPANDED): New Game dialog gains Time Control
      section (5 modes: Untimed/Sudden/Fischer/Bronstein/US-delay);
      live clock display with low-time warning; per-move visual
      annotation caching (_computeAndCacheVisualAnnotations) for
      [%csl]/[%cal] export.
  - chess.src/ai-bridge.js (EXPANDED): _buildPGNString() now emits
      [TimeControl "..."] header when timed; per-move comments now
      include [%emt] (untimed) or [%clk] (timed) plus [%csl]/[%cal]
      from the visual annotations cache.
  - stats.html (EXPANDED): New "Visual Annotations" stats section
      tallies [%csl] G/B/R/Y counts and NAG $1-$6 distribution.
  - chess.src/chess960.js (from prior v1.0.4 round): unchanged.
  - chess.src/game-logic.js (EXPANDED): added time_control_* i18n
      strings (bilingual zh/en).
  - Version strings throughout: v1.0.3 → v1.0.4 (header badge, about
      dialog, loading title, render-error fallback page).
  - Built chess.html includes all the above via build-chess.py.

v1.0.4 changes (reflected in stats.html and rebuilt chess.html):
  - chess.src/chess960.js (NEW FILE): Chess960 implementation.
  - chess.src/pgn-standard.js (NEW FILE): standardized PGN encoder/decoder.
  - chess.src/ai-bridge.js: _buildPGNString() rewritten to emit
      Seven-Tag Roster + supplementary tags via composePGN().
  - chess.src/tablebase.js: fenToState() detects Shredder-FEN castling
      rights; _parsePGN() extracts [Variant "Chess960"] tag; importPGN()
      sets gameVariant + calls setChess960Mode(true).
  - chess.src/game-logic.js: Chess960 UI i18n strings; loading_title → v1.0.4.
  - chess.src/ui.js: New Game dialog Chess960 toggle + SP-ID selector
      + back-rank preview; _startGameImpl() branches on dlgChess960.
  - chess.src/index.html.tpl: <title>Regalia v1.0.4</title>.
  - stats.html: Heatmap Control Statistics section (per-square avg
      control, strongest/weakest squares, center-control trend).
  - All i18n strings bilingual (zh/en).

v1.0.3 changes (reflected in stats.html and rebuilt chess.html):
  - stats.html: NEW time-management analysis feature.
      extractMoveTimes(pgnText) parses per-move thinking times from PGN
      comments. Two conventions are supported:
        1. v1.0.3 direct format: `{3.2s +0.5 略优}` (time + space + eval).
           No header needed; the `<number>s` pattern is the move's used time.
        2. Standard PGN clock format (requires [TimeControl] header):
           `[%clk HH:MM:SS]` gives the player's REMAINING clock after the
           move. The app parses `[TimeControl "BASE+INC"]` to get the base
           time and per-move increment, tracks each player's previous
           remaining clock (initialized to baseTime), and derives used time
           via `used = previousClock + increment - currentClk`. Three
           TimeControl notations are supported: "7200+60" (base+increment),
           "1800" (base only), "40/7200" (moves-per-time, treated as no
           increment). Without a [TimeControl] header, [%clk] values are
           recorded as clock-remaining only — not used to derive used time.
           If a move has both a {N.Ns} direct comment and a [%clk], the
           direct format takes precedence.
      Also recognizes the earlier em-dash format `{<sec>s——...}` for
      backward compatibility, and standard `[%clk HH:MM:SS]`.
      The Time Management section shows: total/White/Black time used,
      average per move, slowest/fastest move (with move number), time
      volatility (standard deviation), long-think count (>10s), quick-move
      count (<1s), phase distribution (opening/midgame/endgame), and an
      SVG bar chart of per-move thinking time. When a [TimeControl] header
      is present, a blue info bar at the top lists the base time and
      per-move increment.
  - stats.html: NEW clickable variation moves.
      Previously only mainline moves were clickable for per-position
      statistics. In v1.0.3, variation moves inside `(...)` are also
      clickable. On click, selectVariationMove(varId, varMoveIdx) builds
      a synthetic move sequence: mainline[0..mainIdxBefore-1] + ALL
      variation moves[0..varClickedIdx] (the ENTIRE series from the
      variation's first move to the clicked move, not just the clicked
      move). mainIdxBefore is the index of the mainline move that the
      variation's first move REPLACES (the move immediately to the LEFT
      of `(`). The synthetic sequence is then used for ALL stats
      computation. Variation moves from index 0 to varClickedIdx are
      visually highlighted (class "var-included" for moves before the
      clicked one, "selected" for the clicked one) to communicate that
      the entire series is being used.
  - stats.html: Variation text rendered in italic.
      The `.pgn-display .variation` CSS rule now includes `font-style:italic`
      so the `()` parentheses and all content inside are visually distinct
      from mainline moves.
  - stats.html: NEW FEN panel below the PGN text panel.
      renderFENPanel() generates a FEN string from the selected move's
      post-state via stateToFEN(state). The panel shows the FEN of the
      position right after the selected move (mainline or variation),
      with a copy-to-clipboard button. If no move is selected, shows the
      initial position FEN + a hint.
  - stats.html: NEW selection banner.
      A small banner above the PGN text panel shows the currently selected
      move number (mainline or variation), making it clear which position
      the stats below correspond to. For variation selections, the banner
      shows the RANGE of variation moves (1 to N) and the total count,
      explicitly noting that the entire series replaces the single
      mainline move.
  - stats.html: v1.0.3 FIX — clear stale moveRecords on PGN import.
      When a new PGN is imported (via _statsPastePGN or onStatsPGNFileRead),
      _payload.moveRecords and _payload.evals are now cleared to null.
      Without this clear, parsePGN() would detect the stale moveRecords
      from the PREVIOUS game and call parseFromMoveRecords() — replaying
      the old game's moves instead of parsing the newly imported PGN text.
      This was the root cause of "imported PGN not recognized": the
      metadata (headers) was extracted from the new PGN (correct) but the
      moves/positions came from the old game's moveRecords (wrong), and
      [%clk]/[TimeControl] time analysis showed the right times but for
      the wrong number of moves. Also clears _variationMoves and
      _variationMeta to reset the variation-selection state.
  - stats.html: Bilingual UI strings added for all new features (fen_label,
      fen_hint, fen_copy, time_*, time_control_header, time_base_time,
      time_increment, variation_marker, select_hint, select_var_hint, etc.)
      — supports the existing ↔️ Chinese/English language toggle.
  - chess.src/ai-bridge.js: _buildPGNComment() format uses a single space
      as separator between thinking time and eval annotation.
      Examples:
        "{3.2s +0.5 略优}"   (time + short eval)
        "{3.2s SF18 D22 +1.0 8%W/91%D/1%L}"  (time + full SF18 line)
        "{3.2s}"             (time only — no trailing space)
        "{+0.5 略优}"         (eval only — no separator)
  - chess.src/ui.js, game-logic.js, index.html.tpl: version strings
    updated from v1.0.2 → v1.0.3 (header badge, about dialog, loading
    title, built_in_only string, <title>).

v1.0.3 patch changes (version number unchanged — still v1.0.3 / versionCode 103):
  - chess.html (rebuilt from chess.src/):
      * PGN import: Type A variations (alternatives to the owning move)
        are no longer incorrectly relocated to the next move. App-exported
        PGNs with variations now round-trip correctly on re-import.
      * PGN import: embedded [FEN] header support — the FEN's
        fullMoveNumber is used as the starting move number for the move
        list, review mode, and PGN export.
      * Landscape review layout: removed the max-width cap on .review-moves
        so the move list takes all remaining horizontal space (was capped
        to board_width - 8px, wasting hundreds of pixels on tablets/wide
        screens). Also removed the 360px hard cap on board width.
  - No changes to stats.html in this patch.
  - No changes to AGPLv3_Logo.svg or GPLv3_Logo.svg.

v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev23 changes:
  - chess.html (rebuilt from chess.src/):
      * Eval cache writes now debounced (150ms) instead of synchronous on every
        set()/delete() — batch analyze-all performance improved ~60x for large
        caches.
      * Engine restart no longer wipes the entire persisted eval cache — only
        the current game's requested-step is reset, preserving other games'
        evals (Stockfish is deterministic).
      * saveEvalCacheSync (Java side) now uses Files.move with ATOMIC_MOVE on
        API 26+ — eliminates the delete+rename data-loss window.
  - No changes to stats.html, AGPLv3_Logo.svg, or GPLv3_Logo.svg.

v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev24 changes:
  - chess.html (rebuilt from chess.src/):
      * Analyze-all interruption root-cause fix (5 bugs): all-cached instant
        completion, per-step 60s safety timer with skip-stuck-step, batch
        resume on engine auto-recovery, cache-hit advance during batch,
        onEngineError no longer drops batch.
      * Instant cache restoration from PGN comments: _parsePGN() extracts
        [%eval ...] tags from {} comments; importPGN() populates
        _reviewEvalCache so positions with eval annotations are shown
        instantly without calling the engine.
      * PGN cache archive completeness: _pgnCacheSaveCurrent() always uses
        _buildPGNString(true) — saved PGN includes variations (forced on),
        comments with [%eval]/[%emt]/[%clk]/[%csl]/[%cal], Seven-Tag Roster.
      * Player rename feature: clicking "你"/"You" on the player bar opens a
        rename prompt; name persists via persistentSet('Regalia_humanName')
        and is used in all PGN text ([White "..."]/[Black "..."]).
      * Removed redundant 📥 Import button from PGN Cache Manager.
      * New i18n keys: rename_player_hint, rename_player_prompt,
        rename_player_saved, rename_player_reset (zh/en).
  - No changes to stats.html, AGPLv3_Logo.svg, or GPLv3_Logo.svg.

v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev25 changes:
  - chess.html (rebuilt from chess.src/):
      * New Game dialog: removed redundant <h3> heading above Chess960
        dedicated settings ("菲舍尔任意制象棋"/"Fischer Random Chess"). The
        Chess960 toggle label already makes the mode clear; settings now
        appear directly under the toggle.
  - stats.html (GPL v3):
      * renderPGNText() → renderSAN(): promotion symbols now rendered as
        side-colored piece symbols (♕/♛, ♖/♜, ♗/♝, ♘/♞) instead of literal
        letters. Previously, pawn promotions (e.g. "e8=Q") only prepended
        the pawn symbol but left "=Q" as text. Now "e8=Q+" → "♙e8=♕+" (White)
        / "♟e8=♛+" (Black). A shared _replacePromo() helper handles both
        pawn-move and piece-move branches uniformly, including check/mate
        suffixes (+/#).
  - No changes to AGPLv3_Logo.svg or GPLv3_Logo.svg.

v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev26 changes:
  - stats.html (GPL v3):
      * renderPGNText() — ROOT-CAUSE FIX for "e8=Q still shows letter" bug.
        Rev25 added _replacePromo() to convert =Q/=R/=B/=N to symbols, but
        the promotion still showed as a letter because the SAN regex never
        captured the promotion suffix for non-capture pawn promotions.
        The pawn non-capture alternative was [a-h][1-8][+#]? (NO promotion
        group), so "e8=Q" matched only "e8" — leaving "=Q" as raw literal
        text. Rev26 fixes the alternative to [a-h][1-8](?:=[QRBN])?[+#]?,
        which captures the full "e8=Q". Same fix applied to the variation-
        move regex. Now ALL promotion formats render with piece symbols:
        e8=Q → ♙e8=♕, exd8=R → ♙exd8=♖, a8=N# → ♟a8=♞#, b1=B+ → ♙b1=♗+.
  - No changes to chess.html, AGPLv3_Logo.svg, or GPLv3_Logo.svg.

v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev27 changes:
  - chess.html (rebuilt from chess.src/, GPL v3 + AGPL v3 combined work):
      * Hyperlink click handler: new global document-level click handler
        intercepts all <a href="http(s)://..."> clicks anywhere in the
        document (About dialog, license links, etc.) and routes them to
        AndroidBridge.openUrlInBrowser(). The default WebView navigation
        is suppressed via preventDefault(). In-page anchors (#) and
        non-http(s) schemes are left alone.
      * About page GitHub link: the "Source code: https://github.com/YDW99/Regalia"
        line is now a real <a> hyperlink (previously plain text). New i18n
        keys about_source_code_prefix and about_source_code_url split the
        string so the URL can be a link. All license links (AGPL, GPL) now
        also have rel="noopener" for defense-in-depth.
      * 🏳️ Resign feature (DeepSeek review 2.1): new 🏳️ Resign button in
        the player bar next to the "Your turn" indicator. Confirmation
        dialog (showResignConfirm state) with Yes/Cancel buttons.
        _resignGame() function: sets _resignWinnerColor (the AI's color),
        stops the engine (stop command + isAIThinking=false), stops the
        game clock, sets gameOver + _gameOverStatusKey='resign', plays a
        "lose" sound + ERROR haptic. New i18n keys: resign_btn,
        resign_confirm_title, resign_confirm_msg, resign_yes, resign_no,
        white_resigns, black_resigns, resigns_suffix (zh/en).
        _gameOverStrFromStatus('resign') returns the resigner color +
        "认输"/"resigns". formatEval resign case now uses
        _resignWinnerColor directly (was incorrectly trying to detect
        "White wins" in the resign text).
      * PGN resign export (ai-bridge.js _buildPGNString): [Result] set
        from _resignWinnerColor (1-0 if White wins, 0-1 if Black wins).
        [Termination "Resignation"] supplementary tag added. Last move's
        comment appends "White resigns." / "Black resigns." per the 元宝
        PGN report.
      * _resetGameUIState() resets showResignConfirm=false and
        _resignWinnerColor=null to prevent the previous game's resign
        state from leaking into the new game.
      * handleBackPress() closes the resign confirmation dialog on back
        button press.
  - stats.html (GPL v3):
      * Backspace global interceptor (Kimi P0 fix): the keydown listener
        now checks if e.target is INPUT/TEXTAREA/contentEditable and
        returns early, allowing normal text editing. Previously,
        Backspace in any input field would (1) preventDefault the
        character deletion AND (2) bounce the user back to the main game.
      * applySANMove king-safety validation (Kimi P0 fix): new
        _isKingSafe(state, defenderColor) helper checks if any opponent
        piece can pseudo-legally attack the defender's king. applySANMove
        now calls this AFTER each candidate move and only accepts the
        move if the king is safe. Castling also validates post-castle
        king safety. If a disambiguated piece fails, the scanner
        continues to the next matching piece (correct SAN behavior).
      * game complexity threshold (Kimi P1 fix): validEvals.length>=3
        changed to >=2. With 2 evals, changes has 1 element — avgChange
        and variance are well-defined (variance=0). The previous >=3
        check skipped the entire complexity section for 2-eval games.
      * _escFEN escaping (Kimi P1 fix): added " and ' escaping, matching
        chess.html's _esc() behavior. Closes a potential XSS vector
        where a malicious FEN could break out of HTML attribute context.
      * exportFullHTML regex (Kimi P1 fix): replaced the lazy
        [\s\S]*?\n} regex with a new _stripFnBody() helper that does
        brace-depth counting to find the function's true closing brace.
        The lazy regex could match a nested object literal's closing
        brace, leaving orphaned code in the exported HTML.
      * Board display (DeepSeek review): new _renderStatsBoard(parsed)
        function renders a small chess board ABOVE the PGN text panel
        showing the position after the currently-selected move (or
        initial position). Uses the SAME color scheme as chess.html
        (SQ_LIGHT/SQ_DARK gradients, coordinate labels with stroke,
        piece symbols with color/stroke/glow). White at bottom, Black
        at top. Responsive (max 360px, aspect-ratio 1:1). New i18n key
        position_board (zh: 当前局面, en: Current Position).
      * Hyperlink click handler: new global document-level click handler
        (installed once in init() via _statsLinkHandlerInstalled flag)
        routes <a href="http(s)://..."> clicks to the new
        AndroidBridge.openUrlInBrowser() bridge method.
  - No changes to AGPLv3_Logo.svg or GPLv3_Logo.svg.

v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev28 changes:
  - chess.html (rebuilt from chess.src/, GPL v3 + AGPL v3 combined work):
      * Stats↔main PGN sync (ai-bridge.js openStatsPage): now ALWAYS
        rebuilds the PGN from the current moveRecords via
        _buildPGNString(true) (forceIncludeVariations=true). Previously
        used _cachedOriginalPGN which became STALE when the user played
        new moves after importing. Now the stats page always reflects
        the current main/review game state. Falls back to
        _cachedOriginalPGN only if _buildPGNString returns empty (e.g.,
        FEN-only imports with no moveRecords).
      * _showStatsImportBackPrompt(pgnText) function (ui.js): called
        from MainActivity.onResume() via evaluateJavascript when
        StatsActivity.importedPGNOnStats is non-null. Uses the existing
        _withPGNSaveCheck mechanism to show the "💾 Save PGN file?"
        prompt before importing (if the current game has move records).
        The pending action is importPGN(pgn). New state variable
        _pendingStatsImportPGN stashes the PGN text for the import
        action closure.
      * Game-over emoji fix (ui.js): the game-over overlay's emoji was
        hardcoded to show 🤝 for all non-checkmate terminations. Now
        shows 🏳️ when _gameOverStatusKey==='resign' (matching the
        resign button's icon), and 🤝 only for genuine draws.
      * Stats board promotion fix (tablebase.js _parsePGN): the
        moveRecords.push({...}) in the PGN import path was missing the
        promotion field, so openStatsPage() serialized move records
        without promotion info, and the stats page's executeMove()
        couldn't apply the promotion (showed a pawn on the back rank
        instead of the promoted piece). Fixed by adding
        `promotion: move.promotion||null` to the pushed move record.
      * New i18n keys (game-logic.js): stats_import_back_title,
        stats_import_back_msg, stats_import_back_yes, stats_import_back_no,
        stats_import_back_cancel, stats_import_back_no_pgn (zh/en).
  - stats.html (GPL v3):
      * New state variable _statsImportedPGN — the PGN text imported on
        the stats page (via 🗃️ Paste PGN or 📂 Select PGN File). Set by
        _statsPastePGN() and onStatsPGNFileRead().
      * returnToGame() and requestReview() now intercept when
        _statsImportedPGN is non-null: instead of directly closing the
        stats page, they call _showStatsImportBackPrompt() which shows
        the "🗃️ Import PGN to game?" Yes/No/Cancel dialog.
      * New _showStatsImportBackPrompt() function — renders the
        Yes/No/Cancel dialog with the app's dialog style (.dov/.dlg/.dlg-btns).
        Yes = AndroidBridge.setImportedPGN(pgn) + closeStatsPage.
        No = closeStatsPage without setting the imported PGN.
        Cancel = do nothing (stay on stats page).
      * New _statsImportBackDismiss() function — removes the import-back
        dialog. New _statsImportBackDialogVisible flag prevents
        duplicate dialogs.
      * The dialog's overlay backdrop click = Cancel (stay on stats page).
  - No changes to AGPLv3_Logo.svg or GPLv3_Logo.svg.

v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev29 changes:
  - chess.src/ (see chess.src/README.license for per-file details):
      * CRITICAL: tablebase.js — PGN import failure fix. Rev28's
        `promotion: move.promotion||null` referenced undefined `move`
        (loop variable is `parsedMove`). Fixed to
        `(parsedMove&&parsedMove.move&&parsedMove.move.promotion)||null`.
      * CRITICAL: stats.html — en passant support added to
        canMoveTo() and executeMove() (was missing, caused 25-move
        cascade failure when importing PGNs with en passant).
      * stats.html — checkmate symbol '#' now properly emitted by
        buildSAN() (was always '+'); uses in-place simulation to
        avoid recursion stack overflow.
      * stats.html — classifyMove() NAG Black-side fix: uses
        side-relative moverDelta for ALL mate-threshold comparisons
        (Black's mating move was misclassified as $4 blunder).
      * stats.html — _renderStatsBoard() caption respects
        parsed.isBlackToMoveStart (was using wrong parity for
        black-to-move-start games).
      * stats.html — PGN parse error now localized (was hardcoded
        English "PGN parse error"). New i18n key pgn_parse_error.
      * ai-bridge.js — NAG classification Black-side fix (same as
        stats.html classifyMove).
      * ai-bridge.js — variation prefix falsy-0 fix.
      * tablebase.js — unclosed `{...}` comments now consume rest of
        movetext (PGN spec tolerant behavior).
  - chess.html: rebuilt from chess.src/ changes.

v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev30 changes:
  - chess.src/ui.js (GPL v3): ROBUSTNESS — scroll position restoration
    fix. Added _scrollRestoreGuard flag that suppresses _onMlistScroll
    during programmatic scrollTop restore (was being corrupted by
    intermediate 'scroll' events from scroll-behavior:smooth
    animation). Save phase reads scrollTop DIRECTLY from the live DOM.
    scroll-behavior temporarily switched to 'auto' during restore.
    Same pattern applied to .review-body in review mode.
    _scrollRestoreGuard reset on new game.
  - chess.src/chess960.js (GPL v3): ROBUSTNESS — randomSPID() modulo
    bias elimination via rejection sampling (was `buf[0]%960` with
    ~0.03% bias; now only accepts values < 65280 before %960).
  - chess.html: rebuilt from chess.src/ changes.

v1.0.4 Round-5 Rev31 changes:
  - chess.src/ (see chess.src/README.license for per-file details):
      * ai-bridge.js: UCI COMPLIANCE — startPonder() now passes time
        params for timed games.
      * tablebase.js: removed unused _unclosed flag.
      * pgn-standard.js: removed dead ch==='\s' comparison; fixed
        composePGN leading blank lines.
      * game-logic.js: review mode orientation-change scroll fix.
  - stats.html (GPL v3): _renderStatsBoard() piece sizing fix. Was
