v1.1.0 Phase 57 (2026.7.4):
  - chess.html: rebuilt from chess.src/ (Phase 57 ui.js fixes).
  - ui.js changes: (1) portrait review move-list scroll positioning — replaced
    offsetTop with getBoundingClientRect to compute the active move's position
    relative to .review-moves (not relative to .review-overlay). In portrait,
    offsetTop included the board's full height (256-320px), causing the active
    move to be clamped to scrollHeight-clientHeight (scrolled to bottom) and not
    centered. (2) visual-annotation cache residue fix — enterReview clears the
    '_initial' cache key at entry; _computeInitialPositionAnnotations reads
    reviewStates[0].state (initial position) instead of gameState (live mid-game
    state). Stale '_initial' cache previously caused wrong annotations at step 0.

v1.1.0 Phase 56 (2026.7.4):
  - chess.html: rebuilt from chess.src/ (Phase 56 ui.js + ai-bridge.js fixes).
  - ui.js changes: (1) landscape review nav-button scroll-to-top fix (replaced
    scrollIntoView with manual scrollTop on inner .review-moves only); (2) first-move
    timing sync (_turnStartTime + gameClocks reset in _resetGameUIState).
  - ai-bridge.js changes: PGN timeout annotation ([Termination "Time forfeit"] tag +
    {<color> wins by timeout} last-move comment).

v1.1.0 Phase 55 (2026.7.4):
  - stats.html: executeMove() and buildSAN() castling detection fix. Replaced
    _destEmpty with _destValid — in Chess960, the king's destination square may
    be occupied by the participating rook (e.g. king on d1, rook on c1, O-O-O
    puts king on c1 = rook's source). The old _destEmpty check rejected this
    case, causing the king to "self-capture" the rook and silently lose it from
    the statistics board. Now the participating rook is found FIRST, then the
    destination is validated (empty OR contains the participating rook). Also
    fixed a latent rook-source clearing bug when _rookFrom === _rookTo (rook
    stays in place, e.g. rook on f1 castling kingside to f1).
  - chess.html: rebuilt from chess.src/ (Phase 55 game-logic.js _castleSide fix).

v1.1.0 Phase 54 (2026.7.4):
  - ui.js + index.html.tpl: custom slider (track/fill/thumb divs + transparent
    native input overlay) for pixel-perfect alignment with eval trend chart.
    Slider wrapper CSS identical to chart container. Thumb center via CSS
    calc(3px + ratio * (100% - 6px)).
  - ui.js: move-list scroll-into-view fix (only scroll if not visible,
    _lastReviewStepScrolled moved inside rAF callback).
  - ui.js: executeMove async-callback try-catch.
  - ui.js: ChessAudioEngine partial-init field reset + setEnabled/setVolume
    null-guard.
  - ui.js: render() retry-loop guard (_animRetryCount, max 10).
  - ai-bridge.js: heartbeat timestamp in all engine callbacks (onEngineProgress,
    onBestMove, onHintMove, onPonderProgress).
  - ai-bridge.js: MultiPV secondary-variation divergence fix (distinguish
    alternative vs continuation).
  - tablebase.js: PGN cascade-skip threshold 5 → max(15, len*0.1).
  All changes in GPL-v3-licensed files.


v1.1.0 Phase 53 (2026.7.3):
  - chess.html rebuilt (Phase 53 changes in chess.src/ui.js, chess.src/game-logic.js,
    chess.src/index.html.tpl).
  - stats.html: visual_annotations_desc text updated (escape path → check-response
    path, mentioning king escape + capture-the-checker). green_arrows_escape label
    updated: zh "绿色箭头 (避将路径)" → "绿色箭头 (应将路径)", en "Green Arrows
    (Escape Path)" → "Green Arrows (Check-Response)". Added _slicePGNAtMove(pgnText,
    moveCount) helper inside renderStats — walks the raw PGN text tracking tag-pair
    stripping, brace-comment depth, semicolon comments, variation depth, NAGs,
    move numbers, and SAN move tokens; truncates after the Nth mainline move's
    trailing {...} comment and/or $N NAG (the "move block"). The visual annotations
    stats block now uses this sliced text when a mainline move is selected
    (_selectedMoveIdx >= 0, no variation/FEN selected), so the [%csl]/[%cal]
    counts respect the selected-move cutoff — consistent with the other stats
    blocks that use effectiveParsed.moves. Comment for the [%cal] color semantics
    also updated: "G=escape path" → "G=check-response (king escape or capture the
    checker)".

v1.0.9 Phase 52 (2026.7.2):
  - chess.html rebuilt (Phase 52 changes in chess.src/tablebase.js,
    chess.src/game-logic.js, chess.src/index.html.tpl, chess.src/ui.js).
  - stats.html: PGN tag-stripping regex fix (single-line PGN) + brace-comment
    stripping space-replacement + executeMove castling detection hardened
    (requires king on home row + correct distance + empty destination +
    castling right present in LOCAL state — was: any king move to col 6/2).
  - chess.html rebuilt again (Phase 52 supplement: tablebase.js variation-comment
    isolation fix + importPGN isCheck/isCastling fields added; ui.js chart point
    outline now theme-aware; index.html.tpl dark-mode chart palette unified
    blue-vs-red).
  - stats.html: executeMove now clears castling rights on king/rook move +
    rook capture (robustness, was missing).
